      <title>161: Interfaith Dialogue: Co-Exist or Convert?</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TheIlluminedHeart/~3/QKA6aZsmw2k/161_inter_faith_dialog_co_exist_or_convert</link>
     <guid isPermaLink="false">http://ancientfaith.com/podcasts/illuminedheart/161_inter_faith_dialog_co_exist_or_convert#9151</guid>
 <description>Fr. Alexander Goussetis, priest, comparative religion professor, and interfaith dialogue participant and advocate, speaks with host Kevin Allen about his views on the purpose of interfaith dialogue with Jews, Muslims, and other non-Christians. Kevin asks: Does the Gospel call us to merely understand the faiths of non-Christians, to enter into dialogue with them with no agenda, or is the goal always to try to win those we dialogue with to Christ? Is it "Orthodox" to proselytize, or simply to be a holy witness? These and other questions will be addressed in this program.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
