      <title>157: The Spiritual Guide in Eastern Orthodoxy</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TheIlluminedHeart/~3/3zd62K3a62Y/the_spiritual_guide_in_eastern_orthodoxy</link>
     <guid isPermaLink="false">http://ancientfaith.com/podcasts/illuminedheart/the_spiritual_guide_in_eastern_orthodoxy#8687</guid>
 <description>Host Kevin Allen speaks with Father Steven Tschlis about the role of the spiritual guide - father or mother - in the Eastern Orthodox tradition, and how such a guide may differ from one's parish priest or sacramental confessor. Should we look for a "spiritual father or mother" in a monastery? What role does the parish priest play? These and other questions will be addressed in this conversation.&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
