      <title>142: Mystery and Sacramentality: East and West</title>
      <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/TheIlluminedHeart/~3/ExYAYJixPas/mystery_and_sacramentality_east_and_west</link>
     <guid isPermaLink="false">http://ancientfaith.com/podcasts/illuminedheart/mystery_and_sacramentality_east_and_west#965</guid>
 <description>What began as a conversation with Fuller Theological Seminary professor Dr. Paraskeve (Eve) Tibbs over coffee, becomes an interview on the essential differences between the ways the Christian East and West understand the fundamentals of the faith, worship, and sacraments. A great introduction to East-West Christian distinctives on this encore presentation of The Illumined Heart with Kevin Allen!&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
